# Changelog

All notable changes to cozip are documented here. The same version stamp
applies to every binding (C library, Python, R, Julia) since they share
a single source of truth at `cozip/VERSION`.

The format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/).
Versioning is [CalVer](https://calver.org/) `YYYY.M.D`.

## [2026.5.2] — 2026-05-02

### Added

- `core/libzip/` and `core/zlib/` — vendored upstream sources
  (libzip 1.11.4, zlib 1.3.1) with hand-written cross-platform
  `config.h` and minimal per-library `CMakeLists.txt`. No more
  `FetchContent`, no network during build.
- `cozip_version_string()` declaration in `core/cozip.h` (the
  function was implemented but never declared, breaking strict
  consumers).
- `make wasm` target — builds `cozip.{js,wasm}` via Emscripten into
  `javascript/wasm/`. Confirms portability to browser/Node/webR
  runtimes; outputs are gitignored, regenerated on demand.
- `cozip/javascript/` placeholder directory with a README documenting
  the JS-binding pathway. No public API yet — that work is deferred
  until a concrete use case appears.

### Changed

- `core/CMakeLists.txt` rewritten — uses `add_subdirectory(zlib)` and
  `add_subdirectory(libzip)` against the vendored sources. Visibility
  rules tightened so the final `cozip.dylib`/`.so`/`.dll` exports
  exactly the 8 public `cozip_*` functions and nothing else.
- `Makefile`: `BUILD_DIR` moved from `build/lib/` to `core/build/`,
  matching the principle that the C build artifacts belong inside
  `core/`.
- `release.yml` rewritten without FetchContent assumptions, ~3 min
  faster per platform. Added a symbol-isolation check that fails the
  build if any non-`cozip_*` symbol leaks into the shared library.

### Removed

- `core/cozip.c`: dead helper `get_u64()` (never called by any code
  path; would have been needed only if the writer parsed ZIP64 LFH
  extras, which it doesn't).

### Fixed

- Final `.dylib`/`.so` no longer re-exports libzip and zlib symbols.
  The previous build leaked hundreds of `_zip_*`, `_inflate_*`, and
  `__tr_*` symbols into the cozip ABI, risking clashes with consumers
  that linked a different libzip through another path.

## [2026.5.1] — 2026-05-01

### Added

- R binding (`cozip/r/`) with FLAT-profile `create()` and low-level
  `.Call` shims to `cozip_plan` and `cozip_finalize`. Vendored copies
  of `cozip.{c,h}` in `r/src/` are kept in sync with `core/` by
  pre-commit, not symlinks (CRAN/Windows refuse symlinks).
- `Makevars` generates `r/src/version.h` at compile time from
  `$(PACKAGE_VERSION)` (which R extracts from `DESCRIPTION`). Header
  never lives in git.
- `.pre-commit-config.yaml` runs `make sync-check` whenever `VERSION`,
  `r/DESCRIPTION`, or `core`/`r/src` source files change. Fail-mode,
  no auto-fix — divergence must be resolved consciously by running
  `make sync`.
- `cozip/Makefile` gets `sync-version`, `sync-c`, `sync-check`, plus
  an `all` target that runs `sync + lib + py-install + r-build` for
  full pre-push validation.
- R binding is auto-built by r-universe from the `cozip/r` subdirectory
  via `packages.json`; cross-platform binaries (Linux + macOS + Windows)
  available at `https://asterisk-labs.r-universe.dev`.

### Changed

- `core/version.h.in` simplified to emit only `COZIP_VERSION_STRING`.
  `MAJOR`/`MINOR`/`PATCH` integer macros removed — nothing in the
  codebase consumed them.
- Python `cozip.__version_c__` removed from the public API. With
  coordinated releases it always equals `__version__`; keeping both
  was misleading. `__version__` remains.
- Python `__all__` now includes `read` (was missing while `create`
  was present — inconsistent).
- Python `_resolve_lib_path()` no longer recursively scans `build/`
  directories as a fallback. Could silently load stale `.so` files
  from previous builds; `make py-install` now reliably populates
  `_lib/` so the canonical path is enough.
- `cozip/Makefile` reads version from `cozip/VERSION` directly.
  Previous version parsed `pyproject.toml`, which now uses dynamic
  version, so the regex returned empty and `make sdist` produced
  `cozip-source-.tar.gz`.
- CI architecture collapsed: `ci.yml` deleted, single `release.yml`
  triggered only by version tags. Removed `reuse-lib` (downloading
  libcozip from previous releases when `core/` was unchanged) — the
  bookkeeping wasn't worth ~5 min saved on releases that happen
  every few weeks.

### Removed

- `tools/sync_version.sh` — replaced by `make sync-version`.
- `tools/gen-version.sh` — replaced by inline generation in
  `Makevars`.
- Symlinks from `r/src/cozip.{c,h}` to `core/` — CRAN rejects them
  and they break Windows builds. Replaced with physical copies kept
  in sync by pre-commit.
- `r/src/version.h` from git — generated at compile time, ignored.
- `R CMD check` job from CI — r-universe runs the canonical
  cross-platform check on every push.

### Fixed

- `Makevars` now correctly orders the build: `version.h` is generated
  before any `.c` is compiled, and both `cozip.o` and `cozip_glue.o`
  are listed in `OBJECTS` so neither is silently skipped.

## [2026.4.30] — 2026-04-30

### Added

- `cozip/VERSION` as the single source of truth for the version string,
  read at build time by every binding. CMake parses it before
  `project()`; hatchling reads it via `[tool.hatch.version]` with
  `path = "../VERSION"`; future R and Julia bindings will read the
  same file via their own configure scripts.
- `cozip_version_string()` C API. Returns `COZIP_VERSION_STRING`
  populated from `cozip/VERSION` at compile time. Useful for FFI
  bindings to verify the loaded library matches their expectations.
- Generated header `cozip/version.h` with `COZIP_VERSION_MAJOR`,
  `COZIP_VERSION_MINOR`, `COZIP_VERSION_PATCH`, and
  `COZIP_VERSION_STRING` macros.
- Python: `cozip.__version_c__` attribute exposes the version reported
  by the loaded `libcozip` binary (mostly for debugging — `__version__`
  remains the canonical version users care about).
- Python: PyPI metadata — `readme` rendered on the project page,
  `license = MIT`, authors (Roy Yali, Cesar Aybar, Julio Contreras),
  keywords, classifiers, and project URLs.
- CI: `.github/workflows/release.yml` — tag-driven release pipeline
  with libcozip reuse. When `cozip/core/**` is unchanged since the
  previous tag, libcozip binaries are downloaded from the previous
  GitHub Release instead of recompiled, saving ~12 min per release
  for Python-only patches.
- CI: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — path-based gating per binding via
  `dorny/paths-filter`. PRs touching only Python skip the libcozip
  matrix build and pull the binary from the latest published release.

### Changed

- Python wheels are now tagged `py3-none-<platform>` instead of
  `cp312-cp312-<platform>`. Because cozip uses cffi in ABI mode
  (`ffi.dlopen` at runtime) the wheel is genuinely Python-version
  agnostic, so 4 wheels cover Python 3.10–3.14 across all platforms
  rather than requiring 16 separate builds.
- macOS wheel platform tag relaxed from `macosx_14_0_arm64` to
  `macosx_11_0_universal2`, matching `CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=11.0`
  and the universal binary content. Intel Macs on macOS 11+ now also
  receive a wheel.
- Linux wheel platform tag now `manylinux_2_28_<arch>` (via
  `auditwheel repair`). PyPI rejects the bare `linux_<arch>` tag that
  hatchling produces by default.
- `pyproject.toml` migrated from `version = "..."` static to
  `dynamic = ["version"]` reading from `../VERSION`.
- `cozip/core/CMakeLists.txt` no longer hardcodes `VERSION 1.0.0`.
- CI architecture: `pywheels.yml` removed; its responsibilities are
  split between `ci.yml` (validation, no publish) and `release.yml`
  (build + publish, tag-only).

### Fixed

- PyPI upload no longer emits `long_description missing` warnings.
  Both `README.md` and `LICENSE` are force-included in the wheel root
  and the sdist.
- The sdist is now self-contained: `../VERSION`, `../README.md`, and
  `../LICENSE` are absorbed into the archive root via
  `[tool.hatch.build.targets.sdist.force-include]`.
- Previous `ci.yml` referenced `cat VERSION` from the repo root, which
  silently fell back to `0.0.0-dev` since `VERSION` lives at
  `cozip/VERSION`. The new `release.yml` reads `cozip/VERSION`.

## [2026.4.29] — 2026-04-29

### Added

- First public release.
- `libcozip` C library implementing the Cloud-Optimized ZIP v1.0-draft.4
  specification: `__cozip__` index entry at byte 0, FNV-1a 64 integrity
  hash at LFH bytes 43–50, profiles `NONE`, `FLAT`, and `TACO`.
- Python bindings (`cozip` on PyPI) with cffi ABI-mode loading of the
  bundled native library. Public API: `cozip.create()`, `cozip.lib`,
  `cozip.ffi`, `CozipError`.
- Cross-platform builds: Linux x86_64 + aarch64 (manylinux_2_28),
  macOS universal2, Windows x86_64.
- Vendored zlib v1.3.1 and libzip v1.11.4 via FetchContent for a
  self-contained shared library that depends only on libc.
- GitHub Release with `libcozip-<version>-<platform>.{tar.gz,zip}`
  archives for C-standalone consumers.

